<main class="container">
  <section>
    <%= image_tag(asset_path("home/logo.webp"), alt: "FortressOne logo", height: 128, width: 128) %>

    <hgroup>
    <h1>FortressOne</h1>
    <h2>Quake Team Fortress Remastered</h2>
    </hgroup>

    <p>Free and open source fork of the original 1996 QuakeWorld mod Team Fortress. Fast-paced, class based, arena first person shooter remastered with refined graphics, new mechanics and evolved gameplay.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="grid">
      <div>
        <hgroup>
        <h2>Download</h2>
        <h3>Extract and run</h3>
        </hgroup>

        <p>Latest release (9th August 2021):</p>

        <ul>
          <li><a href="https://github.com/FortressOne/fte-config/releases/download/1.1.1-beta.1/fortressone-fte-windows-1.1.1-beta.1-portable.zip">Windows v1.1.1-beta.1</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://github.com/FortressOne/fte-config/releases/download/1.1.1-beta.1/fortressone-fte-linux-1.1.1-beta.1-portable.zip">Linux v1.1.1-beta.1</a></li>
        </ul>

        <p>Optional extras:</p>

        <ul>
          <li><a href="https://fortressone-share.s3.ap-southeast-2.amazonaws.com/hivis.zip">Hi vis models pack</a></br><small>Extract to <code>FortressOne/fortress/</code></small></li>
          <li><a href="https://fortressone-share.s3.ap-southeast-2.amazonaws.com/quake106_deiced.zip">Shareware Quake v1.06</a></li>
        </ul>

        <p>Pick-up games are organised on <a href="https://discord.fortressone.org">Discord</a>.
      </div>
      <div>
        <%= turbo_frame_tag :live_player_show, src: live_player_show_path, loading: :lazy do %>
          <%= render "video_frame", locals: { h2: "Watch", h3: "loading..." } do %>
            <div aria-busy="true" class="responsive-iframe"></div>
          <% end %>
        <% end %>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

